is deposited in the collection of the 
<materialsCitation id="3B10D857FFC00A2075B53B0BAD1AFEF5" collectionCode="SMNH" pageId="8" pageNumber="234" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="paratype">
<collectionCode id="ED694ACFFFC00A2075B53B0BA85EFEA9" box="[949,1033,259,285]" country="Sweden" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/8z6v-f8is" name="Department of Paleozoology, Swedish Museum of Natural History" pageId="8" pageNumber="234">SMNH</collectionCode>
; 
<specimenCount id="9D7E1983FFC00A2072143B0BA8EAFEA9" box="[1044,1213,259,285]" pageId="8" pageNumber="234" type="generic" typeStatus="paratypes">three paratypes</specimenCount>
are deposited in the collection of the
</materialsCitation>
<collectionCode id="ED694ACFFFC00A2077543B2FADE0FEF5" box="[340,439,295,321]" pageId="8" pageNumber="234">TSUMZ</collectionCode>
. All specimens are preserved in 70% solution of ethanol with a drop of glycerol.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3628181FFC00A2076C73B43AD9FFE3D" pageId="8" pageNumber="234" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BC7D20AFFC00A2076C73B43AD9FFE3D" blockId="8.[151,1437,150,717]" pageId="8" pageNumber="234">
<emphasis id="B90C0E18FFC00A2076C73B43AD19FED1" bold="true" box="[199,334,331,357]" pageId="8" pageNumber="234">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name 
<taxonomicName id="4C78A989FFC00A2074253B43AE9AFED0" authorityName="Ermilov &amp; Starý" authorityYear="2022" box="[549,717,331,356]" class="Arachnida" family="Galumnidae" genus="Pergalumna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="234" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paratsavoensis">
<emphasis id="B90C0E18FFC00A2074253B43AE9AFED0" box="[549,717,331,356]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="234">paratsavoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
refers to the similarity between the new species and 
<taxonomicName id="4C78A989FFC00A2073133B43AD93FE3D" authority="Mahunka, 1986" authorityName="Mahunka" authorityYear="1986" class="Arachnida" family="Galumnidae" genus="Pergalumna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="234" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tsavoensis">
<emphasis id="B90C0E18FFC00A2073133B43AD5DFE3C" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="234">Pergalumna tsavoensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE9AFFBFFC00A2077113B67AD93FE3D" author="Mahunka, S." box="[273,452,367,393]" pageId="8" pageNumber="234" pagination="77 - 102" refId="ref14132" refString="Mahunka, S. (1986) Studies on the oribatid fauna of Kenya (Acari: Oribatida) II. Folia Entomologica Hungarica, 47 (1 - 2), 77 - 102." type="journal article" year="1986">Mahunka, 1986</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3628181FFC00A2076C73B9BAC9AFD79" pageId="8" pageNumber="234" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC7D20AFFC00A2076C73B9BAC9AFD79" blockId="8.[151,1437,150,717]" pageId="8" pageNumber="234">
<emphasis id="B90C0E18FFC00A2076C73B9BAD6CFE19" bold="true" box="[199,315,403,429]" pageId="8" pageNumber="234">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C78A989FFC00A2077443B9BAE29FE18" authority="Ermilov &amp; Starý, 2022" authorityName="Ermilov &amp; Starý" authorityYear="2022" box="[324,638,403,429]" class="Arachnida" family="Galumnidae" genus="Pergalumna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="234" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paratsavoensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B90C0E18FFC00A2077443B9BAE29FE18" box="[324,638,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="234">Pergalumna paratsavoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B90C0E18FFC00A2074863B9BAEB6FE19" bold="true" box="[646,737,403,429]" pageId="8" pageNumber="234">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23FB363FFC00A2074863B9BAEB6FE19" box="[646,737,403,429]" pageId="8" pageNumber="234" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is morphologically most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C78A989FFC00A20727A3B9BAC98FE65" authority="Ermilov &amp; Stary, 2018" authorityName="Ermilov &amp; Stary" authorityYear="2018" class="Arachnida" family="Galumnidae" genus="Pergalumna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="234" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jenoi">
<emphasis id="B90C0E18FFC00A20727A3B9BA898FE18" box="[1146,1231,403,428]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="234">P. jenoi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE9AFFBFFC00A2072D83B9BAC98FE65" author="Ermilov, S. G. &amp; Stary, J." pageId="8" pageNumber="234" pagination="201 - 222" refId="ref13464" refString="Ermilov, S. G. &amp; Stary, J. (2018) New taxa of oribatid mites from Korup National Park (Cameroon). The genus Pergalumna (Acari, Oribatida, Galumnidae), with description of three new species and a key to known species from the Ethiopian region. Zootaxa, 4425 (2), 201 - 222. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4425.2.1" type="journal article" year="2018">Ermilov &amp; Starý, 2018</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C78A989FFC00A2077043BBFAE11FE65" authority="Mahunka, 1986" authorityName="Mahunka" authorityYear="1986" box="[260,582,439,465]" class="Arachnida" family="Galumnidae" genus="Pergalumna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="234" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tsavoensis">
<emphasis id="B90C0E18FFC00A2077043BBFADC6FE64" box="[260,401,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="234">P. tsavoensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE9AFFBFFC00A2077973BBFAE11FE65" author="Mahunka, S." box="[407,582,439,465]" pageId="8" pageNumber="234" pagination="77 - 102" refId="ref14132" refString="Mahunka, S. (1986) Studies on the oribatid fauna of Kenya (Acari: Oribatida) II. Folia Entomologica Hungarica, 47 (1 - 2), 77 - 102." type="journal article" year="1986">Mahunka, 1986</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(see also 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE9AFFBFFC00A2074B23BBFAFDCFE65" author="Ermilov, S. G. &amp; Tolstikov, A. V. &amp; Salavatulin, V. M." box="[690,907,439,465]" pageId="8" pageNumber="234" pagination="63 - 70" refId="ref13807" refString="Ermilov, S. G., Tolstikov, A. V. &amp; Salavatulin, V. M. (2014) Supplementary description of two galumnid mites, Pergalumna tsavoensis and P. bifissurata (Acari, Oribatida, Galumnidae). Acarina, 22 (2), 63 - 70." type="journal article" year="2014">
Ermilov 
<emphasis id="B90C0E18FFC00A2075143BBFAF13FE65" box="[788,836,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="234">et al</emphasis>
. 2014
</bibRefCitation>
) from the Afrotropical region in the presence of dentate anterior margin of ventral margin. However, the new species differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C78A989FFC00A2072293BD3A82AFE40" authorityName="Ermilov &amp; Stary" authorityYear="2018" box="[1065,1149,475,500]" class="Arachnida" family="Galumnidae" genus="Pergalumna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="234" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jenoi">
<emphasis id="B90C0E18FFC00A2072293BD3A82AFE40" box="[1065,1149,475,500]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="234">P. jenoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the larger body length (680–796 versus 481–597), minute (versus long) interlamellar seta, large (versus small) notogastral porose areas, long (versus short) dorsophragma, comparatively short (versus long) adanal setae 
<emphasis id="B90C0E18FFC00A20722D382BA81EFD89" box="[1069,1097,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="234">ad</emphasis>
<subScript id="17FCD04FFFC00A207249383DA806FDF7" attach="left" box="[1097,1105,565,579]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="234">1</subScript>
and 
<emphasis id="B90C0E18FFC00A207287382BA8F4FD89" box="[1159,1187,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="234">ad</emphasis>
<subScript id="17FCD04FFFC00A2072A3383DA8FCFDF7" attach="left" box="[1187,1195,565,579]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="234">2</subScript>
, the presence (versus absence) of dorsosejugal and postanal porose areas, and the absence (versus presence) of dorsosejugal suture, lack of reticulate pattern on pteromorph and striate sculpturing on genital plate; from 
<taxonomicName id="4C78A989FFC00A2072133863A8F6FD30" authorityName="Mahunka" authorityYear="1986" box="[1043,1185,619,644]" class="Arachnida" family="Galumnidae" genus="Pergalumna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="234" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tsavoensis">
<emphasis id="B90C0E18FFC00A2072133863A8F6FD30" box="[1043,1185,619,644]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="234">P. tsavoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the pointed (versus rounded) rostrum, minute (versus long) interlamellar seta and the presence (versus absence) of postanal porose area.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
